HEADWORD: Melanconiales
<hw>Mel`an*co`ni*a"les</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. <ets>Melanconium</ets>, name of the typical genus, fr. Gr.
<grk>me`las</grk> black + <?/ dust, in allusion to the dark
spores.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The smallest of the three orders
of Fungi Imperfecti, including those with no asci nor pycnidia, but as a
rule having the spores in cavities without special walls. They cause
many of the plant diseases known as
<causes>anthracnose</causes>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Melanesian</ent>⟦br⟧
